The issue was the /login/callback route from Okta was hitting agentmesh-dev-ai.calix.local but only the UI service HTTPRoute had that hostname. The auth service HTTPRoute (/oauth path) only had agentmesh.dev.ocp-ai.calix.local — so when Okta redirected back to agentmesh-dev-ai.calix.local/login/callback, the Gateway accepted the TLS connection (listener matched) but Envoy couldn't find a matching route for the auth path, returning route_not_found. The browser showed an SSL warning because the auth flow was failing, not because the certificate was bad.
Once you added agentmesh-dev-ai.calix.local to the auth service HTTPRoute with the correct parentRef, the full auth flow worked end to end — TLS terminates with the corporate cert, the UI route serves the page, and the auth callback route handles the Okta redirect. No broken links in the chain.
